		<h3>Daily Fiction</h3>
		<h1>The Pohaku</h1>
		<h2>By Jasmin 'Iolani Hakes</h2>
		<div class="img-excerpt-container">
			<div class="img-container"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/pohaku.jpg" alt="The Pohaku"></div>
			<div class="excerpt-container"><div class="excerpt"><em>The following is from Jasmin 'Iolani Hakes's </em>The Pohaku<em>. Hakes was born and raised in Hilo, Hawai’i. She is the author of the novel </em>Hula<em>, and her essays have appeared in the </em>Los Angeles Times<em> and the </em>Sacramento Bee<em>. She is the recipient of the Best Fiction award from the Southern California Writers Conference, a Squaw Valley LoJo Foundation Scholarship, a Writing by Writers Emerging Voices fellowship, and a Hedgebrook residency. She worked throughout college as a professional luau dancer. She lives in California.</em></div></div>
		</div>
